cloudy- very windy s/w 13-18. Have lite rain for the past week and lots of wind
Sunny 15mph west wind have had cloudy rainey days- very cool weather nights and days
sunny west wind 8-10 mph lots of pine pollen and poplar cotton in the water lite foam at shore. water temp surface62.2 15 ft. 59.5
sunny wind s/w 3-5 lots of pine pollen in water have had lots of rain. So far very little foam. Low boat traffic
sunny.5-8 N. west wind still lots of pine pollen in water. some foam- low boat traffic- very cool weather.
wind west 7-9 sunny. Lots of pine pollen in water was surprized to get a deep reading. some foam low boat traffic
wind W 1-3. Had lite rain the past week. High boat traffic the 4th weekend. Lots of fireworks debris in lake bottom. some foam and pine pollen yet. Water temp 63.6 surface and 63.3 at 15 ft.
P/S N. wind 9-12 mph heavy boat traffic this past weekend. Some lite rain showers
Sunny- wind N. 3 MPH. Landstat path 25 today. Water temp surface 72.3 at 15 ft. 71.4 some foam again- low boat traffic.
P/C wind S. 8 mph. Lots of foam coming ashore again. Heavy thunder storms 2 days ago. Lite boat traffic for the week.
Sunny wind S/W 10-12mph Some foam. Had cool weather temps.and lots of lite rain. Heavy boat traffic this weekend
cloudy. wind S.W. 15-18 mph. No foam- cool weather- no boat traffic.
cloudy. E.wind 5-10 Lake very low- no boat traffic- water temp at surface 64.7 at 15 ft. 64.4
Sunny S.W.wind 10-15 mph. Lots of foam- no boat traffic- have had strong winds the past week and a half
Sunny no wind lake is very low don't get the much needed moisture anymore
some foam for the past three weeks- lots of cold damp weather
some pollen in water. lots of foam yet- some boat traffic over the weekend- a very cool and damp weekend
still lots of pollen in the water- surface temp 71- some foam still.
partly cloudy wind N. 12mph air temp60 degress had 2 inches and 2 tenths rain the past two days still lots of pine pollen in water
Still lots of foam-lake way below normal-very high temps strong winds lots of evaporation- low boat traffic
air temp 84 wind N.E. 2 mph. no foam. lots of boat traffic- lake went way down hot windy days no rain lake now a l.5 ft below normal
Had a long time of hot humid days.  Lots of foam.  Very heavy boat traffic.  Mostly jet skis.  Lake getting very low.
Still some foam- air temp 72- wind w.3mph lake getting very low- lots of boat traffic this past weekend.
n.w. wind 1-3mph lake still going down.
N.W.wind 3-5 mph no foam- water very low still hot windy days.
wind S 2-5 mph. We got 10 inches of rain the 4 + 5 of Oct. Lake is still below normal but did come up some.
partly cloudy- air temp 54F- lots of foam and pine pollen- W wind 5-8mph
partly cloudy- wind calm- no boat traffic yet
sunny- wind S 10 mph. Little boat traffic- lots of foam and heavy pine pollen
partly cloudy- wind S 15 mph- lots of pine pollen and lots of algae in the lake- no boat traffic
wind S 8-10mph- lots of hot windy days- lots of foam- no boat traffic
Sunny wind N.3-5 mph. Lake is very muddy looking. Reason unknown
Sunny Hot Air temp82 wind S. 1-5 mph. Lots of snails again Bad looking water. One year ago today S.D. was 14.5 Ft. Why the difference now
Cloudy wind calm still lots of foam and alge. Lot of jet ski traffic and big boats
Sunny wind N.W. 2-3 mph. Still lots of foam and alge. Lots of snails.
P/C wind E 3 mph Lake still dirty looking lots of snails
Wind N. 5-8 Sunny Water starting to clear a little. Still lots of snails and foam
P/C wind south 6 mph Still lots of snails lake looks dirty
sunny wind S 3-4 mph still lots of snails  No more foam
X88 banded swan was on our lake one evening. The lake is very low again. No foam still lots of snails
Sunny S wind 5-8 some foam air temp 32 still lots of snails had 3 inch of snow fall 2 days ago
sunny- s/w wind 10-15 some foam. some pine pollen- two loons are back on the lake haven't nested so far.
wind dead calm- no foam- no new snails so far- lots of pine pollen
wing 3-5 S. lots oc pine pollen- no new snails- some alge- loons had one chick born the 0610.
Sunny- wind calm- loons had two chicks as of 0611.heavy pine pollen- lots of small fish dead floating.
Sunny- wind S.W. 4-7 mph- lots of pine pollen- some foam- lots of jet ski and big boat traffic this past week.
Sunny no wind lake is clearing up just a little alge. No foam or snails. Lake is getting very low. It gets lower each year lower than the year before

sunny wind calm no foam or snails. alge seems to be very light no pine pollen. lake is getting real low deep hole is now only 15 feet instead of 17 feet that it was a few years ago. two baby loons are growing fast and getting big.
Sunny- wind calm- heavy boat traffic.- no foam a few snails

sunny wind W 3-5 mph. some snails coming into shore now- some foam- Lake is going down fast with no rain. I now have 36 feet of new land from the normal water mark. I can't get into my boat now I have to use knee boots and drag out the boat. I have 63 feet of dock starting at the normal water mark and at the end of 63 feet I have 5 inches of water.
Wind is W. to NW 8-10 mph. Sunny. Have had sunny hot weather all summer no rain to speak of. Snails are down a little from last year. Lake is still going down every day.
Sunny wind calm lake still going down every day. More snails coming in now. A little more alge in the water now.
Sunny- wind S at 3-5 mph. Lots of sea gulls out on the lake. Not many new snails coming into shore now.
Sunny Wind South at 7 mph. Some suspended alge. A few more snails coming into shore.  Very little boat- jet ski traffic now. lake still getting lower each day.

Air temp 42 wind W. at 8-10 mph. still some alge. water level still going down. I now have near 40 ft of new beach- have trouble getting boat out into floatable water. The deep hole has gone from aroung 16 ft down to 14ft. most docks around the lake are not standing in water anymore. Baby loons did good this summer and still living.
wind S/W 3-5 mph. Sunny Lake has come a little from some rain still very low. Loons are gone now.
sunny- wind S.E. 3-5 mph some brown foam by shore
wind N at 3-6 mph. Some pine pollen on shore water. Loon nested Fri the 23rd. wind N 3-6 mph some pine pollen on shore water. Loon nested Fri the 23rd.
wind W 5-8 mph. Sunny We had a pair of swans on the lake the past two days one is banded. No boat traffic- High winds for three days
Wind N 8-11mph Sunny had high winds the past 7-8 days and lots of cloudy days. No foam - lots of pine pollen no boat traffic
Wind N/W 3-5 mph Sunny lots of pine pollen in water. Still no heavy boat traffic or jet skis.
Sunny wind calm no boat traffic. Had a lot of high windy days with white caps- lots of cloudy days and some rainy days. The baby loon is growing up fast and getting big. No foam or snails.
Sunny- wing N. 3-4 mph. No foam or pine pollen. Very little boat traffic.
Sunny wind N at 3 mph we had a heavy rain storm past week dumping over 2 inches of rain in a short time. lots of run off. Baby loon is about full size. Still not much boat traffic.
Sunny wind calm. Lake is going down fast- having trouble getting my boat out from shore. Baby loon is still with us.
Sunny- wind S. 4-6 mph. Lake is very low for a seepage lake we are not getting any ground water and very little rain. The loons doing fine.
Sunny wind N 3-5 mph. had a good rain fall Sat night.  Air temp 47
Sunny S. wind 3-5 mph A swan on the lake yesterday the 2th not banded
cloudy wind west 1-3 mph. some foam early morning. no boat traffic.
Wind S. 5-7 mph Sunny no boat traffic lots of pine pollen in the water
Sunny N-NW wind 1-3 mhp lake still going down. No boat traffic very few snails this summer.

Sunny- wind N 3-7 mph. Lots of boat traffic and jet ski traffic the 4th weekend. Still some suppended pine pollen floating in the water. Lake is still going down. Most of the lake people have started their docks at the waters edge and now have sections on dry land.
wind S 1-2 mph sunny some boat traffic new weed beds coming up
wind N NW 12mph. Sunny. Very little boat traffic some lite rain the past days. Day temps 70s to mid 70s.
Wind S. 3-=5 mph Lake getting very low now mostly muck sand and rock bars are above water some areas people can't get their boats out they are parked on the sand flats quite a ways from the house.
Sunny wind N. 1-2 mph very little foam on the water this summer. Some boat traffic mostly jet skis The lake is still going down more each day.
Sunny wind calm lite boat traffic. Lake still going down.
Sunny wind calm no foam 12 days no rain
loons back on lake the next day after ice out
Partly sunny wind S. 2-3 mph. Lake still going down each season. In 1999 deep hole was at 16.5 today deep hole is at 14.5. most docks are going in at the edge of water cause of large beaches
Sunny SW wing 10-15 mph no boat traffic yet.
Sunny wind north 1-3 mph lots of boat traffic this past weekend. some floating alge. Loon is on the nest with one egg in nest.
N. wind 3mph partly sunny no boat traffic. The male loon doesn't have any leg banding- I think it is the male. The female is still on the nest.
sunny wind west 3-5 mph. loon still on the nest. some jet ski and boat traffic.  air temp 79.5 degrees.
N wind 5-8 mph Sunny very little boat traffic due to very low water levels. Loon still on nest with two eggs.
Sunny wind W 3-5 mph not much boat traffic over 4th of July. Some recent rain lake is holding not losing so far.

Wind calm- air temp73.7 had a lot of jet ski and big boat traffic the past week and weekend. Had a good rain this weekend. Lots of sediment floating. Weed beds in new areas Two baby loons still alive.
Sunny  Wind W. 3-5 mph. Baby loons are diving now still being feed by parents. Lake has little traffic
Sunny Wind N. 4-7 mph Have had some bad rain storms and wind again High temps in the mid 80s and very humid. Baby loon still doing fine

sunny windy west wind 9-15 mph. Baby loons are still being fed by their parent. The are getting bigger everyday. Have had a lot of hot humid days temps in the upper 80s and windy. today temps 50 degrees.
Sunny Wind South 5-10 mph. Have had a lot of rain and some storms. Loons still O.K.

Sunny wind N.W. 7 mph. Lots of foam this past week. I can only find one baby loon I think the eagles got one the other day as they were harrassing them the other day.  Had a bad storm last night straight line winds over 60 mph.
Sunny wind W NW at 16-21 mph some foam at shore. Baby loon fishing on its own away from parents. air temp 59 degrees
Sunny wind W 1-3 mph lots of fine supended alge some foam. Finally found the second baby loon. The eagles didn't get it the parents are gone now
Calm no wind Sunny temp is 43 degrees some foam all week. Trees at height of color. Baby loons are gone.
Ice out April 21 the loons back April 17 some open water out in the middle total ice out the 21st. Some foam on and off - very windy cold rainy days. The lake is up 14 inches from last fall.

calm no wind sunny. The lake has come up another good inch with last 2 and 3/4 inches of rain. It is now up a little over 15 inches up from last fall.  The loons still are not nesting both swimming together.
wind 6-8 mph sunny. The loon has nested been on the nest for several days now. Water is coming futher up the beaches now since we have been having more rain and very cool temps.
Sunny wind S at 3 mph. Loon is still on the nest. We had two days this last week of very strong winds it did stir up the lake a lot.
Sunny wind S.E. 9 mph Loon still on the nest very little rain for the past three weeks the lake has gone down 5 inches.
Partly sunny wind E. at 5 mph. We had a lot of rain the last two days lots of run off. One baby loon was born today. Some foam on the water.
N. wind 1-3 mph sunny- The baby loons growing big fast. Lake is starting to go down again very hot dry weather and no rain.

No wind very calm. Partly sunny. Had a bad wind rain storm last night got 1inch and 6 tenths of rain. The loons are doing fine so far. wind calm partly sunny. We got a bad rain and wind storm last night received 1+6 tenths inches of rain. The loon family is doing fine
wind 3-5 mph sunny the baby loons are doing fine
Wind south 3-5 mph Sunny lots of surface foam loons doing fine
sunny wind S. West 2-3 mph lots of brown fine alge- lots of boat and jet ski. traffic the past week
Wind south 2 mph. Sunny the lake is down 6 inches due to a month of no rain and hot humid temps. The loons are still doing good. some lite alge in the water.

Wind W at 3 mph. Sunny. Loon came back April 13th and a few days later he had a girlfriend. Had a pair of swans on the lake for a few days. We are getting some nice rain amounts the past two weeks.  The lake is now 16 ft at the deep hole.
Sunny wind south 21-23 mph. Lake still holding at 16 feet at the deep hole. The loon is now on the nest.

Sunny wind north west 5-8 mph there is some marble size alge red in color floating around. The loon is finally staying on the nest now. The lake came up 4 inches is now 16 foot 4 inches at the deep hole. We need another foot to be back at normal
Wind dead calm-  cloudy we have had a long hot sunny windy dry spell lake went down to 15ft 11 inches. loon still on the nest. no boat traffic yet.
wind south 3-4 mph. sunny and hot. The loon is still on the nest. Very little boat traffic for the week

Wind north 3-5 mph. Partly cloudy. Some big boats on the lake. Very dry- hot temps in the high 80s very windy the lake is going down again went down 6 inches since last time out. Now 15.10 feet deep hole. Loon had a bad egg so no little one this year.
sunny wind calm lots of boat traffic lots of brown alge. Got some much needed rain for 3 days
Wind north 6-8 mph sunny. Still lots of boat traffic and jet skis this past week The lake is at 15.7 ft at the deep hole. Loons still around
sunny wind 7mph north to north west. loons still here lake down to 15ft 7inches. No heavy boat traffic this past week
Wind North at 5 mph sunny. No boat traffic all week. Lake way down 15 ft 0 inches. Loons still on the lake.
Sunny wind North 8 mph. Some alge and foam. Loons appear to have left the lake. Lake depth way down deep hole only 14 ft

lots of poplar tree residue on the lake water. The lake level is now at 14ft 10in. It has come up from last fall when it was 14ft the last time I check. Sunny day wind calm no boat traffic.   secchi reading hit bottom 14ft 10inches
Sunny Wind 8 - 10 mph from the east. no boat traffic Secchi 12 feet
lots of pine pollen in the water- water is very green in by shore. Lake level holding at 14ft 10inches. Sunny day wind from south at 8 - 10 miles per hour.

Wind calm and sunny. Still lots of pine pollen in the water. Several high power jet skis tearing the sand grass bottom. It looks like someone is dumping the lawn clippings in the water. The operators are cutting tight circles to jump the waves. Lake has come up a little possibly from lots of rain and maybe some ground water. The lake is now up to 15ft 2inches.

Sunny wind south west at 5 mph. Very hot already this morning. We have had 6 days of very wind days- very humid days- and very hot days up into the 80s most of the time and not cool nights. The lake has gone down 4 inches in this heat.
Partly cloudy wind north 16 - 20 mph. Lake is still holding at 14ft 10 inches despite hot and very windy days and high humidity.

sunny wind N/W 6-9 mph. lake level at 14ft 11-1/2 inches. some rain on and off. Had four loons drop in the lake in front of me as I was going back to shore. Seemed very tame as they came along side of boat and swam with me as I was going very slow. Followed me for some time.

sunny wind from the west 6mph. Lots of boat traffic from 4ht July till the second week in August now all is quiet. Weather has been windy- sunny- and no rain to help the lake. lake level is now 14ft 6in
Sunny wind out of the North at 8 mph. Loons still here. No boat traffic lake is quiet. Our humming birds have left now not coming to the feeders anymore.
Sunny wind south west at 3-5 mph. Lake depth at 14 feet. Lots of residue floating on the surface. Adult loons are gone left the end of Sept. Young loon is still here.
Wind NNW 10-15 mph partly cloudy. The lake has come up some to 15 feet 4 inches. The loons are close to the island and should start nesting soon.
Wind south 4 to 7 mph sunny some pine pollen on the water. Loons still haven't nested yet. Water depth holding a little over 15 feet 4 inches.
wind N. 3 - 5 mph. Sunny Lots of pine pollen on and in the water is all green. The loons still haven't nested. Very little boat traffic.
wind south 3-5-mph. Cloudy no boat traffic. Can't find the loons anywhere on the lake. Lake is holding at 15 feet 4 inches. Plenty of rain for the month of June.

sunny wind NW at 9 mph. lake is down to 15 feet down 4 inches. Had some very windy hot days lake went down fast. The loons didn't nest this year they are still on the lake as a couple. Lots of algae in the water column.

Sunny wind South 10 - 12 mph. Not much boat traffic since the 4th of July. We have had lots of windy days and sunny all day. That took more water out of the lake. The lake is down 9 inches since spring. It now measures 14 feet 7 inches. The loons are still here on the lake no chicks this year. Lots of foam in by shore.
Wind N. 2 mph. Sunny nice day. Yesterday we got a 6 tenths inch of a down pour rain. Today the lake is up 4 inches to 14 ft 11 inches. Loons still here no nest this year.

Sunny wind from North at 8 - 10 mph. Heavy boat traffic this past weekend. The loons still here. One duck with three young ones and one duck with four young ones. So far the eagles haven't them. Lake has gone down another two inches to 14ft 7inches.
wind s/w at 8 - 12 mph. Had a bad electrical storm and a fast one half inch of rain early morning. The lake has a lot of foam near shore. The lake is up a little to 14ft 9in.

Wind s/w 2-4 mph Sunny The weather hasn't allowed me to check water sooner. Either very windy and cloudy or raining a lot. The lake has come up to 14ft 10inches. Some foam along shore and the loons are still here.

Most docks are out of the lake now and ours goes out this weekend. The loons are still here and now have their gray feathers for winter. Sunny and no wind with lots of rain we have a lake height of 15 feet now.

sunny day wind N 15-20 mph. Two loons now on the lake swimming together. land temp 50 degrees. The lake has come up to 15ft 9in even though  we didn't have a lot of snow this winter just lots of below zero temps some days and most nights.

Sunny the wind n/west at 5-8 mph. We have a different spring this year lots of frost and strong winds making white caps a few days. There has been some foam coming into shore and now the poplar tress are shedding the spring cotton on the water. The lake has come up in spring and is holding it own so far at 15 feet 6 inches but we are still a long way from the high water mark. Yesterday morning and this morning 29 degrees. Several past mornings we were getting snow flakes and some white ground. The loon is now on the nest for the last 4 days.

Sunny lake calm lots of poplar cotton on the water. The loon is still on the nest. We have had lots of rain lately the lake is back up to 15ft 8in. One otter playing and fishing along the shore. Lots of fine algae in the water column.

Sunny wind from the north at 5-8 mph.  A eagle tried to get the nesting loon but didn't succede. In the fight the one egg got flipped out of the nest and broke. There are baby mallard ducks on the lake and a few geese. The last week and one half lots of rain the lake is coming up more than it was this spring. The lake is up to 16 feet deep hole

Sunny wind from the north at 3 - 5 mph. Lots of pine pollen out now everything covered yellow green pollen. Looks like the loon has re-nested. The lake is staying up with all the rain. It is now 16 feet 2 inches. The water column is very green.
Lake very calm- sunny no wind. The loon is still on the nest for the second time water depth is 16 feet. not much boat traffic.

Sunny- wind S/W at 1 mph. Lots of green algae in the water column. The loon is still on the nest just about due for eggs to hatch. Lake is going down a little due to very warm windy days. Lake is now at 15 feet 11 inches. There was a lot of boat traffic for the weekend of the 4th of July.

No wind very calm. Sunny very hot again haven't had rain now for three weeks. Lake is going down it is 15 feet 4 inches. One baby loon hatched over a week ago and growing fast. There are two eagles that keep bothering the loons so far they got most of the baby mallards not the baby loon.

Wind south/west 7-9 mph lots of green algae in the water column very green. Baby loon still alive and growing fast. Sunny and windy. The lake is now down to 15 feet even is still going down due to lack of no rain.

Sunny wind N/W at 5 - 8 mph. The baby loon is doing good still alive the eagle didn't get it yet. It is growing big. There was a lot if foam the last couple of days and the lake is very- very green with alage. We have had many days of strong winds white caps rolling. Not much boat traffic this summer just mostly jet skis. The lake depth is holding at 15 feet.

Wind calm Sunny very bad case of blue green algae could only see the secchi disk down to two feet then it disappeared. The lake is holding at 15 feet. I can't find the baby loon today the parents are still out there.

sunny wind N/W at 3 mph. water very murky blue gray in color lots of foam along shore. Small specks of what ever all over the surface. The baby loon O.K. and only one parent now with baby. The heavy blue green algae is starting to thin out. Have had some rain on and off lake at 15 feet 4 inches.

Wind north at 5 - 8 mph Sunny- the lake starting to clear up from the heavy blue green algae. The foam is almost all gone now. lake depth is at 14 feet 10 inches. Still had a lot of warm very windy days.

Sunny wind 2 mph from the south. the lake is up this year to 15ft 9in in the deep hole. the lake has a lot of pine pollen floating and in the water depth. the water is yellow green. the loon is on the nest again this year no black flies so far.
Wind south west 7mph- Sunny- Loon still on the nest. water level 15ft 6in we have very windy sunny days this past week.

Sunny wind s/w at 7.4 mph- pine pollen gone for now. Loon still on the nest. A big flock of geese landed on the lake this morning. Have had some good rain lake back up to 15ft 9in. Lake very quiet no boat traffic and now bad weeds spoted

Wind calm- sunny lots of pine pollen on the surface and in the water column- the lake has come up some with more rain now deep hole at 16ft. The baby loons are doing good last night a rouge loon came on the lake and fought with the father loon. The father loon won the battle. The family of geese there were five little ones now it is down to only three.

Sunny lake calm still lots of green water. One mother duck with three little ducks swimming around. The two baby loons are still here and growing fast two weeks old the 23rd. Lake pretty quiet not much boat traffic just a few fishermen out on the lake. Due to very hot windy days the lake is now at 15ft 11inches at the deep hole

Sunny wind south 2 mph. We have had very hot humid windy days the lake is down to 15ft 6inches. Lots of heavy boat traffic and fireworks on and into the lake. There is a lot of allege in the water low visibility. The two baby loons still alive and doing good now diving and preening and the leg wag. The  babies are now 3 and 1/2 weeks old. Sunny wind south 2 mph. We have had very hot humid windy days the lake is down to 15ft 6inches. Lots of heavy boat traffic and fireworks on and into the lake. There is a lot of allege in the water low visibility. The two baby loons still alive and doing good now diving and preening and the leg wag. The  babies are now 3 and 1/2 weeks old.

Sunny wind south west 1 - 2 mph. There is getting a lot green algae in the lake now. The depth is 15ft 11in. The baby loons are doing good so far. More sea gulls are now on the lake. There has been a lot of strong winds and high heat temps.

Sunny wind south east at 2 - 3 mph. Not much boat traffic the past two weeks. Still lots of just green algae in the water. The baby loons are getting  real big now. Otters come and go on the lake. The lake is holding at 15ft 10inches. We have been getting lots of rain to off set the hot humid windy days taking out water.

Sunny wind south 3 - 5 mph. the loons are doing good so far no bad weeds sighted so far. The lake is holding at 16 feet even. Maybe the water tables are starting to fill with all the rain that we had. No blue green algae yet but we have had a lot of sunny very hot days high dew points and high humidity.

Sunny- wind calm- lots of very small white objects covering the entire lake surface. The baby loons doing fine now diving and fishing for themselves. We have had some nice amounts of rain the past days. The depth is still at 16 feet. Have seen on shore some leopard frogs nice size ones.

Partly cloudy- wind south 6 - 9 mph. Lots of green algae now had a lot of very hot windy days some heavy rainy days with run off. The baby loons are still doing good. The male humming birds must have left don't see them by the feeders. The lake is at 15 feet 11 inches.

Sunny- calm no wind The loons are still here the two chicks look good I think the male might left already as I can only find the mother loon and two babies. We have had some rainy days and lots of very windy days white caps rolling. The color is starting to come in on the trees and our humming birds are gone. The lake is holding at 16 feet.

Sunny  Wind east 5 - 10 mph. depth now 16 feet 4 inches lake is coming up good this summer but a long way from the high water mark like years back. The loons mother and babies are still here. Lots of flocks of geese flying south.

Sunny wind south 3 - 5 mph. The two baby loons are still here but I think mom finally left. We had four swans on the lake for a few days now gone. Most docks are in for winter and only a few boats left yet in the water. water depth is

column1: 16 feet 1 inch

column2: Partly cloudy- wind calm There were six swans that landed on the lake the middle of the week. The baby loons are still here as of today and look very healthy. We had lots of rain this past week near four inches and the lake is up to 16 feet 8 inches.
air temp 46 degrees calm and sunny. The loons still have not nested yet the lake has come some since fall.

Sunny very windy at 15 - 20 miles per hour N-NE   We had three days of thunder and lighting storms for over three inches of rain lots of run off and now lots of pine pollen in the water. The lake is now at 17 feet 2 inches high- and pretty cloudy. The loon has nested on May 11th and a small number of geese are on the lake two geese with seven little ones

Sunny- wind west 3 - 5 mph. Lake is still up from lots of rain at 17feet 2 inches. The loon is still on the nest will be due to hatch shortly. Lots of pine pollen on and in the water. Hard to get out to check either cloudy or raining or very windy the lake is now normal height now. No bad weeds spotted in the shallows.

Sunny wind n / nw at 15 - 20 mph  lots of fine green algae in the water- lots of foam on the water and still pine pollen coming down. This summer so far we have had lots of wind some high winds making white caps on the lake and lots of rain and cloudy days making it hard to get out to check the lake. The lake is at 17 feet deep and starting to go into the low beaches there are some docks now under water.   The loon had only one baby this year and the chick is doing good

Sunny very calm no wind. lake is still up at 17 feet deep hole- the baby loon is growing fast. Lots of boat traffic the past week and this weekend. Still getting lots of rain and winds since early spring. The pine pollen is way down making clear water.

Sunny slight breeze and warm day. The lake had heavy large boat and jet traffic this past week. The lake is still up at 17 feet. The baby loon is now diving and trying to fish. I see the mom but not the dad- still have two families of geese on the lake.

Sunny  day- wind from south at 5 mph. Only find one adult loon can't find the baby. We have a lot of big boats with very large motors and very fast jet skis on the lake for the past month and a week. There is lots of the lake bottom floating up on the surface and now there is different areas of water shield weeds taking over the shore line. The lake has gone down to 16 feet 6 inches in the deep hole. Very hot dry month for the month of July.

Sunny wind calm lots of water shield showing up in 6 -8 feet of water in many different areas. The lake is getting very dirty with lake weeds and grass showing up on the surface and on shore lines. The past weeks many boats with large motors and jet skis running during most of the day. The loon still around- humming birds have slowed down feeding

column1: The lake depth is still 16 feet 6 inches

column2: Sunny warm day slight breeze. The baby loon is still here but can't find the mother she was still here last week. The lake went down some 16 feet 8 inches. Had a pair of mink on my dock the other day playing. Deer started to change to the winter coats and the leaves are turning color. There was some foam on the water the other day it was real wavy.

Sunny calm no wind the baby loon is still here and the adult loon is gone now. We had some heavy rain storms and the lake is at 17 feet 1 inch. Lots of fine green algae could be due to lots of rain run off. All ducks and geese are gone now. This is the last report for this season as I am taking out the dock and boat for the winter.

The lake is up from last fall  looks good very near the high water mark. The loons are back and have mated on Sunday the 6th of May. They are now swimming together near the nesting grounds. Saw some pollywogs swimming by shore looked good and healthy. The humming birds came back to the feeders yesterday the 14th of May. Air temp 62 degrees

Lake calm air temp 76 degrees- there are two loons out near the island but not nesting can't find a nest any where. The lake has come up a lot it is at 18 feet 4 inches. some green algae in the water. Lots of leopard frogs by shore and poly wogs by shore also. So far no large boats going on the water.

Sunny- wind from east at 6 - 10 mph still lots of lots of green pine pollen coming down  the loons didn't nest this year don't know why there has been as many as 5 loons at one time on the lake there is still 3 loons on the lake as of today. The lake has come up real good this summer it is now 18 ft 11 in out in the deep hole. Baby fawns running around saw 6 different ones so far.

Sunny -wind calm lake very cloudy with fine algae we have been having many days in the high 80s and white cap wave days it was difficult to get out for some time to check water. The lake has gone down some due the hot days and very windy days it now is at 18 feet even. The loons did not nest this year we do have loons that come and go on the lake this summer. There is lots of frogs this year more than other years

Sunny- wind from the north to northwest at 10 mph. The lake went down some more due to dry hot windy days now at 17 feet 9 inches. Lots of new plants along the shore line most look like they are native to the north. A loon on the lake once in a while don't see the family of geese anymore.

Sunny- calm no wind- water is very green had lots of heavy jet ski and large boats all day past Saturday and Sunday lake bottom got stirred up a lot . The lake is at 17feet 8 inches we need rain it is  are getting real dry. one loon on the lake

wind calm- sunny/cloudy lake has gone down due to no rain for some weeks lake at 17 feet even. Lots of big boat and jet skis out churning up the lake bottom lots of algae in the water. One buck deer out swimming in the lake seem buy a neighbor. Different loons coming and going on the lake seen by neighbors and myself. Different weeds coming up at other shorelines around the lake no invasive weeds found
Sunny slight wind from the east- lots of small surface clutter and fine green algae we got a good rain fall and the lake is up to 17 feet 4 inches. No more boat traffic or fireworks.

loons- geese and swans have been stopping and leaving our island is under water so a loon platform was built and placed by the island in hopes the loons will nest. The days have been warm but most nights are below freezing.

sunny lake very calm did not have good days for taking lake information either cloudy or very windy that is reason for late information.   The loons did not nest as the island is under water and no place to nest a platform was built and put out but is not being used as of today. Lots of cotton from poplar trees on the ground and the lake. I measured 19 feet of depth in the deep hole. One bear came out in front of me the other morning when I was walking just kept walking in front of me didn't know I was behind the it.

Sunny wind south at 5 - 8 mph lots of pine pollen in the water. the loon did lay two eggs on the platform but didn't sit on them at all I don't know if they are no good it is almost a week since laid and no loon sitting on eggs.  the island is still under water so a platform was needed for the loons.  water at the deep hole was 18.6 feet

Sunny wind NNW at 13mph there are several loons on the lake but no eggs hatched this year so no baby loons. not much boat or jet ski traffic on the lake so far this summer. The lake is now at 17 feet 10 inches down from last check at about 7 inches.
The wind south west at 8 mph sunny- the lake has a lot of fine algae floating in the water column green in color.

column1: the lake is down due to a month and half lack of rain just hot temps and sunny all day long. The lake is down to 17 ft.

column2: partly cloudy wind calm trees changing color fast loons might have left already. lake deep hole 17ft  9 inches.

It has been a wild spring rain and very windy lots of days I was late getting the dock and boat in the lake then we got it in and lots of days with white caps rolling.   The loon did nest on the platform built for her but was driven off by all the black flies  a week later she re-nested and has been on the since day one. The lake is very dirty from a lot of green pine pollen and the lake is still up at 19 feet 5 inches  Low boat traffic so far.

Sunny wind south west 9 mph. Still lots of pine pollen falling. The baby loons are doing good with the parents by them. This past weekend lots of jet skis and large inboards out on the lake. Five otters were spotted out in the lake swimming.
Sunny wind south at seven mph water is very cloudy. Low boat traffic this summer depth today 18 feet 11 inches deep hole.
sunny with wind from south west at 10 mph gusts.Water very cloudy lake depth still 19 feet 5 inches have been getting lots of rain lately. The baby loons doing good are now one month old.
Sunny wind south west 7 mph and quite no boat traffic. The baby loons are getting bigger each day.  The lake depth at deep hole was 19 feet. lake is clearing up and cooling down.

Sunny temp 77 degrees no wind lots of run off debris as Friday the 21st we had heavy thunder storms and got 3 and 7 tenths inches of rain in a little over 3 hours.   Plenty of pine pollen also. The lake is very high now due to all the rain this summer.      The baby loons are still o.k. and growing the have been some floater loons landing and then leaving no fighting.       Some of the maple trees are starting to get color and a heavy crop of acorns falling.
Cloudy- calm no wind. Lots of algae in the water found the lake deep hole is 19 feet 8 inches. We have had some heavy thunder rain storms last weekend almost 4 inches in three days

column1: This is my last season of checking the water 21 years of checking and watching for bad milfoil. I will also give up being a loon ranger that also is 21 years of checking. I went to a lot of spring work shops for water and loons  both I learned a lot and passed the information along when people ask mainly about the loons. I hope I found a resident that will take over next year I will help him get started.     Bye for now.
Start Date
